cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.IR 

The paper deals with person Re-Identification, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper proposes a deep learning model, which involves learning feature representations and matching models, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of human part cues to alleviate pose variations, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also involves the use of adaptive feature fusions, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves matching features from different images, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
